node.text:
Follow @dr.raymondgardinier for scientifically proven and evidence based nutrition, mindset, and fitness tips!

Who got in phenomenal shape after just one workout?

Or after eating just one salad?

Or going without one dessert?

No one.

So the “unsexy” secret to success is - your results come from your daily habits.

This is why most programs and diets fail.

Fad diets and extreme workout programs aren’t something most people can stick to for more than a few weeks or months at a time.

So the real question then isn’t “what works?” 

It’s “What works day after day, year after year?”

The answer is whatever you can stick to for the long haul.

Simplicity and convenience is key when it comes to getting consistent with nutrition and fitness.

And when you’re consistent, you don’t have to give up your favorite foods or spend countless hours exercising.

Because that’s just not sustainable.

My go-to smoothie:
1 cup frozen blueberries
1/2 banana
1 scoop creatine
2 scoops protein (not 1)
1.5 cup almond milk
1 tsp cinnamon

Full recipe below, send it to a friend who’d love this!⁣
By: Robin Broadfoot and Tasty

Ingredients (for 8 servings)
VEGGIES
2 eggplants
6 roma tomatoes
2 yellow squashes
2 zucchinis
SAUCE
2 tablespoons olive oil
1 onion, diced
4 cloves garlic, minced
1 red bell pepper, diced
1 yellow bell pepper, diced
salt, to taste
pepper, to taste
28 oz can of crushed tomatoes (795 g)
2 tablespoons chopped fresh basil, from 8-10 leaves
HERB SEASONING
2 tablespoons chopped fresh basil, from 8-10 leaves
1 teaspoon garlic, minced
2 tablespoons Chopped fresh parsley
2 teaspoons fresh thyme
salt, to taste
pepper, to taste
4 tablespoons olive oil

Preparation
Preheat the oven for 375˚F (190˚C).
Slice the eggplant, tomatoes, squash, and zucchini into approximately ¹⁄₁₆-inch (1-mm) rounds, then set aside.
Make the sauce: Heat the olive oil in a 12-inch (30-cm) oven-safe pan over medium-high heat. Sauté the onion, garlic, and bell peppers until soft, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, then add the crushed tomatoes. Stir until the ingredients are fully incorporated. Remove from heat, then add the basil. Stir once more, then smooth the surface of the sauce with a spatula.
Arrange the sliced veggies in alternating patterns, (for example, eggplant, tomato, squash, zucchini) on top of the sauce from the outer edge to the middle of the pan. Season with salt and pepper. Cover the pan with foil and bake for 40 minutes. Uncover, then bake for another 20 minutes, until the vegetables are softened.
Mix herb seasoning ingredients and pour over the cooked ratatouille.
Serve while hot as a main dish or side. The ratatouille is also excellent the next day--cover with foil and reheat in a 350˚F (180˚C) oven for 15 minutes, or simply microwave to desired temperature.
Enjoy!
---

🍤  ZESTY SHRIMP 🍤⁣
1️⃣ SHRIMP: 1 pound wild shrimp (thawed, patted dry, seasoned with salt, pepper, paprika and garlic powder). Heat 1 tablespoon olive or coconut oil over medium high, add shrimp and sauté for about 2 minutes per side. Add 2 teaspoon coconut aminos, a squeeze of lemon or lime juice and some hot sauce and toss. Remove from heat. Top with cilantro or parsley. 2️⃣ BRUSSELS: 1 pound Brussels (trimmed). Bring 2 cups salted water to a boil, add the Brussels and cook for about 4 minutes. Drain water and place Brussels on a paper towel to pat dry. Using a flat bottom cup, “Smash” the Brussels just slightly, one at a time. Add them to a bowl and toss with 1.5 tablespoon olive oil and salt and pepper to taste. Set oven to broil, place the Brussels on a sheet pan and broil for 2 minutes (6 inches from the broiler). Flip then broil for another 1-2 minutes. (Careful not to burn). 3️⃣ POTATOES: slice 1 pound mini gold potatoes multiple times, leaving 1/4 inch at the bottom (TUTORIAL IN HIGHLIGHTS), toss with 1.5 tablespoon olive oil, 2 cloves minced garlic, salt and pepper. Bake on 450 for 35-40 minutes on a sheet or an oven safe pan. 4️⃣ AIOLI: Dressing: 2 tablespoon Dijon mustard, 4 tablespoons greek yogurt (or nondairy), 1 tablespoon mayonnaise, 1 tablespoon coconut aminos, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.⁣

⠀⁣
⠀⁣
It’s finally summer time 😎☀️ So these 4-ingredients-or-less ideas are great additions to your recipe list :) All vegan treats by @plantyou are perfect next time you fancy something sweet for a snack, breakfast or dessert!⁣
⠀⁣
⠀⁣
🍉WATERMELON SORBET🍉⁣
⠀⠀300 CALORIES⁣
Deseed & freeze your watermelon slices. Then blend with your reduced fat coconut cream and lime!⁣
⠀⁣
⠀⁣
🍪OREO SMOOTHIE🍪⁣
⠀⠀350 CALORIES⁣
A healthier recreation of an Oreo Milkshake that is dairy free and the perfect indulgence for a hot summer day✔️Simply add all ingredients to a blender until you achieve smoothie Oreo packed goodness💫⁣
⠀⁣
⠀⁣
🍩VEGAN FUDGE🍩⁣
⠀⠀80 CALORIES⁣
This makes 20 pieces. Simply microwave ingredients until they are combined, then smooth into a pan lined with wax paper. Freeze until firm and enjoy!⁣
⠀⁣
⠀⁣
🥞BANANA PANCAKES🥞⁣
 ⠀⠀300 CALORIES⁣
2 servings. Three ingredients and a blender are all your need for these delicious vegan pancakes!⁣
These pancakes are Vegan, Gluten Free, Healthy, Customisable (adjust toppings|spices) and Fast!⁣
⠀⁣
⠀⁣
🍫RAW BROWNIES🍫⁣
⠀⠀150 CALORIES⁣
Recipe makes 20. Just mix in the food processor. Press into a pan and throw in the refrigerator or enjoy immediately! Perfect for a dessert or a pre-workout snack. ⠀⁣

Go Follow @daveymaher_fitness he works specifically with clients who have hormonal & metabolism issues. DM him “HORMONES”⁣
.⁣
Team Coffee ☕ or Team Matcha 🍵⁣
Credit @miguelthevegan⁣
⁣
Coffee naturally contains more caffeine than matcha, which for some people isn't necessarily a bad thing... The upper daily limit of caffeine recommended for adults is 400mg so roughly 4 cups of caffeinated coffee or 6 cups of matcha a day. Since this may be too much for some people, you have to see how your body and mind reacts to caffeine⁣
⁣
You may want to cut back if you have side effects like:⁣
- Headache⁣
- Insomnia⁣
- Nervousness⁣
- Irritability⁣
- Frequent urination or inability to control urination⁣
- Fast heartbeat⁣
- Muscle tremors⁣
⁣
Matcha contains less caffeine than coffee and due to the amino acid L-Theanine which can increase alpha wave activity in the brain, it may induce relaxation and decrease stress levels, balancing out the effects usually coming from consuming caffeinated beverages⁣
⁣
Coffee due to the above, can thus have a stronger effect while matcha has a calmer effect, not just because of being lower in caffeine but also due to the nutrients present such as L-Theanine⁣
⁣
Subsequently matcha can provide a slower releasing and prolonged energy burst Vs coffee plus it contains x160 more antioxidants making it a healthier choice overall. But bare in mind I'm not saying coffee is unhealthy⁣
⁣
CONCLUSION⁣
- Both are great choices, but see how you react when consuming caffeinated coffee and/or matcha and it affects your well being on a day to day basis⁣
- If you enjoy coffee too much there's no need to switch to matcha, unless you noticed some side effects from consuming coffee⁣
- Drinking caffeinated beverages won't reduce your mortality rate alone since there are many factors that take place such as smoking, alcohol consumption, stress levels, genetics, nutrition, exercise, sleep etc⁣
- My personal recommendation is not to consume any caffeine after 5PM since the effect takes some time to wear off, so it doesn't affect your sleep quality⁣
⁣
#matcha #caffeine #aminoacids #plantbasednutrition #coffee #tea #greentea #energybooster #preworkout

Ingredients⁣
* Tortilla wrap⁣
* Your favorite fillings!⁣
⠀⁣
⠀Instructions⁣
1. DECIDE HOW MANY FOLDS YOU WANT: Whether you want 3 or 4 sections will change how you fill the tortilla wrap, you need to know this in advance.⁣
2. MAKE THE CUT: In the center of the tortilla (or nori/damp rice paper sheet), make a cut outwards to the edge of the tortilla.⁣
3. ADD THE FILLING: Visually divide the surface area into 3 or 4 parts based on the layers you want and place your toppings.⁣
4. FOLD IT: Start by folding the wrap from the left side of your cut and flip and flip again until you have a completely folded tortilla.⁣
5. HEAT IT (OPTIONAL): For a homemade quesadilla style dish, you can not heat your tortilla wrap. Use a sandwich press, grill, or hot skillet and lightly heat for 1-2 minutes on each side, or until lightly browned. You can do this step with or without oil/butter.⁣

node.text:
Follow @Dr.Stefan.Gospodinov for the most SUSTAINABLE health, nutrition, and fitness tips!

You will NEVER have it all figured out. However, as long as you’re continually working on yourself, learning, and making better decisions for you, you are making progress.⠀
.⠀
Great post by @whenharrymetsalad.⠀
.⠀
Let's say you rate your current diet as a 3/10. Then you will only need to reach 5/10 to start seeing a positive change. Many of you will immediately try to go straight from 3/10 to 10/10 and skip out the in-between. It is essential to appreciate the more gradual changes and adapting to them before progressing to the next level so that you don’t get discouraged.⠀
.⠀
Dietary and lifestyle change is hard. Patience and consistency is the name of the game, and success shows up in small ways! Don't be too hard on yourself if you hit some bumps on your journey, and celebrate the small wins. Positive attitudes create positive outcomes.⠀
.⠀
